<L>__{interior albergo goldoni, rome. day.}
<A>__{ripley's battered cases are carried into the tiny lobby of this small hotel. he exchanges his passport at the desk for his room key, then makes his way, carrying his own luggage to the metal cage elevator. this scene intercuts with:}
<L>__{interior hotel grand. day.}
<A>__{dickie's array of leather luggage is pulled along on a baggage trolley by a liveried porter. dickie's passport slides across the marble desk. a key comes back, collected by a hand sporting dickie's two distinctive rings. as aldo, the front desk manager, inspects the passport, he looks at the owner. ripley wears a terrific suit, his hair parted in the greenleaf style, no glasses. his voice, when he speaks, has the same, lazy, confident drawl.}
<C>__{aldo}
<D>__{welcome back, signor greenleaf.}
<C>__{ripley}
<P>__{(walking away)}
<D>__{thank you.}
